Fans were taken down memory lane when Afrobeats veterans, Faze, Adx of now-defunct music duo Artquake, and Konga performed at the June Edition of Ruggedman’s Foundation Night that was held at De Saras Lounge, Lekki Phase 1, Lagos. The event which aims at celebrating the founders of Afrobeats and bringing the new generation to experience live performances by the veterans had its maiden edition in May 2022 where it played host to Durella, Ay.com, Flex B, Leena Martins, and BBNaija’s Ike.   Edochie’s first wife shrugs off marriage drama     Adaorah shines at BET awards     Paul & CeeCee Oniya’s group release Yoruba is my…   Faze headlined the second edition show and performed a series of hit songs including ‘Need Somebody’ and ‘Kpo Kpo di Kpo.’ In the same vein, Konga thrilled fans with his smash hit ‘Kaba Kaba’ while supporting acts like Spider Ridder, Dj Shevco, Whiteman, Hypeman Mc Platg, and Dj Quest entertained guests at the event. Mimickon and BBNaija’s Tuoyo also made surprise appearances.